SENTENCE um because they face little competition and have favorable growing conditions .
SENTENCE but for most species ,  most of the time ,  resources are finite .
SENTENCE there's only so much available which leads me to my point .
SENTENCE every ecosystem has what we call a carrying capacity .
SENTENCE the carrying capacity is the maximum population size of a species that can be sustained by the resources of a particular ecosystem .
SENTENCE resources are ,  of course ,  food ,  water ,  and just as important ,  space .
SENTENCE although every species has a maximum rate at which the population of that species could increase ,  assuming ideal conditions for the species in its environment .
SENTENCE there are always going to be environmental factors that limit population growth .
SENTENCE this is called environmental resistance .
SENTENCE environmental resistance is important becauseit stops populations from growing out of control .
SENTENCE factors such food supply ,  predation and disease affect population size ,  and can change from year to year or season to season .
